title: Fanny Hill
overview: Young, pretty and innocent, Fanny Hill has lost her parents and must find her way in life amidst the perils of turbulent 18th-century London. She's fortunate enough to rapidly find a place as chambermaid of the effusive Mrs. Brown, who lives in a large house teeming with female 'relatives' in neglig√©e and with very relaxed manners. She also insists that Fanny alone meets various gentlemen who show an ardent interest in her.
